                <componentInstanceProperties>
                    <name>richTextValue</name>
                    <value>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b style=&quot;font-size: 13.5pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Event Overview&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Events in Salesforce are meetings that you would like to have associated with Opportunities, Accounts, or Contacts. Events are also how sales activity is measured. Once your Outlook account is synced with Salesforce, you will see the following two calendars on Salesforce’s Calendar tab in the bottom right-hand corner:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Microsoft Office 365: This is your entire ARC Outlook Calendar.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;My Events: This is your Salesforce Calendar.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;To Capture Your Sales Activity:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Use Outlook to create meetings as you always have.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 7pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Salesforce will automatically copy all Events that have at least one external attendee from your Outlook Calendar to your Salesforce Calendar.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Click on the copied Salesforce Event,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 7pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;select ‘Edit’, and fill out the required fields. Events with a status of ‘Completed’ in the Status field will count towards your activity total.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;ql-indent-1&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;u style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Additional Information:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 13.3333px; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;You can add or remove attendees from the copied Salesforce event without updating the Outlook event.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;A list of your uncompleted Events can be found on the Salesforce Home tab.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Under some circumstances an Outlook Event may not be copied over.&amp;nbsp;In this case, simply create a Salesforce Event and complete it.&amp;nbsp;One example of this is recurring meetings, which are not copied over from Outlook to Salesforce.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Events usually sync in a few minutes, but it can take up to a few hours for Outlook Events to be added to your Salesforce Calendar.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;If you create an Outlook Event with external attendees, the Event will sync with Salesforce before they accept your invitation.&amp;nbsp;If you are invited to an Outlook Event, it will sync with Salesforce after you accept.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;If a Salesforce Event is created that you do not need for tracking activity, simply delete it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://web.microsoftstream.com/video/62ab3b6c-b0d6-4e86-9d3d-550f81287019&quot; rel=&quot;noopener noreferrer&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 10pt; font-family: &amp;quot;Segoe UI&amp;quot;, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Screencast Video Overview&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</value>
